inn1.comm: lands on a good length outside off, guided down to third man for a single

dropped, should have been taken, short of a good length, pushes at it from the crease, flew off the outside edge and second slip, Kevin O'Brien's standing there, should have clasped it, timed his jump well but couldn't hold on, immediately apologises to the bowler.
Barresi's taking some hits, short on middle, nips back in and catches him on the rib
straying on the pads, short of a good length, poor line and it deflects off the thighs as he tries to glance it down and rolls down the fine-leg boundary
slightly short on the off, gets forward and taps it into the off side off the back foot

appeal for a catch, short of a good length on the off, gets on the back foot and defends inside the line to that one, there was a sound as it went past the bat towards the keeper, big appeal from the Irish but the umpire declares it Not Out.
goodish length on the off, pushes it off the front foot towards cover
fullish on the off, gets forward to the pitch and drives it firmly towards mid-off

gone, big nick, bowls from slightly wide of the crease, angles it in, lands full outside off and Eric tries to drive it through the line, there might have been a bit of movement away from the bat, gets an edge and Niall O'Brien makes no mistake
good length outside off, holds its line, leaves it alone
lands around a good length outside off, pushes it on the up wide of mid-off for a single
bat hitting the pad there, good length and moved away, that was a beauty, drew him forward and prompted him fish for it, just went past the outside edge
short of a good length outside off, holds its line, leaves it be
nicely played, too straight from Rankin, gets forward and flicks it away past midwicket for a well-timed boundary
Netherlands in early trouble here, short of a good length and it's there to cut but Cooper fails to keep it down, strikes it straight into the hands of point, easy catch, Ireland are in control
just a touch too straight, tucked to midwicket
again Rankin targets the pads, ten Doeschate clips firmly to square leg but Wilson dives to his right to cut the ball off
a rising delivery leaps uncomfortably up into Tendo's ribs, the hand comes off the bat as he drops the ball to leg and they set off for a quick single
hitting the pitch and seaming away off a good length, but wide enough to be easily left alone
past the edge! Johnston went slightly fuller and drew ten Doeschate into a drive, again there was definite movement away from the bat
Johnston is testing ten Doeschate's patience outside off here, this time the batsman leaves

great line from Johnston here! He's just plugging away and letting the pitch to the rest, again he's past the edge but ten Doeschate whips the bat inside the line at the same time, so arguably another leave
much straighter, landing on middle and it's defended back down the track
ten Doeschate comes forward in watchful defence with bat and pad right together, pushing another probing delivery into the covers
bouncer! There's plenty of life in the wicket, and this one bursts over the batsman's head ... actually probably bounced a bit too much, he was easily under it
full on off stump, Kervezee taps just to the left of mid-off and finds enough of the gap for them to sneak a single as the fielder runs round
short and rising, not the bouncer but up into the armpit and pulled down to fine leg
beaten outside off, it was the extra bounce that did it
same shot, forcing off the back foot, but this time he take the bounce into account, deliberately lifting the ball over gully and beating third man too
cracked very hard down the ground this time, the ball being much fuller, but Rankin sticks his right boot out to stop the shot
Johnston continues to send them down on off, ten Doeschate patiently leaves alone
lifted to wide midwicket! Johnston aimed at middle and off and ten Doeschate walked across his stumps, getting inside the line and flicking with plenty of bottom hand to find the boundary
Johnston re-adjusts his line, ten Doeschate taps down to gully
again ten Doeschate walks across to off, trying to upset the bowler's line, but Johnston follows him and the shot is stopped at cover point
too full, ten Doeschate steps forward and drives hard into the ground, the ball bounces up and over a diving cover fielder
aggressive batting! ten Doeschate walks across to off and tries to muscle a length delivery through the leg side ... not much timing in the shot, however, so just the one
good-looking cut pings out of the middle, but third man is wide and sprints round to cut it off
Rankin tries the surprise yorker, but Kervezee jams the bat down in time
whipped off the pad, great fielding from Wilson saves the runs, diving across at midwicket
that is dismissive! Full and wide - a long, floaty half-volley and it's thrashed away with a square drive
very full again, dug out to mid-off
Rankin's been a bit erratic with his lines today, and this one is sprayed well down the leg side
landing on middle and heading towards leg, ten Doeschate clips but finds a fielder in the way of the shot
four runs, but that is streaky batting! Kervezee is turned inside-out by the away movement, he was looking to flick to leg but the ball takes a thick edge and loops down to third man
he's less expansive in the shot this time, stepping forward to defend cautiously to leg
classic line and length stuff from Johnston, Kervezee defends
fuller, this time the ball wobbles a touch in the air as Kervezee leans into a drive, a thick inside edge ricochets into the pad
again Johnston attacks the stumps, straighter this time and Kervezee drives to mid-on
driven on the other side of the wicket this time, but straight to mid-off
fielding! The ball was rocketing to the point boundary ... until the fielder there went airborne to cut it off. Superb fielding covers for some slightly shoddy bowling, that was short and wide
straighter, defended back down the wicket
punched through cover, that's such a difficult shot to play, off the back foot. Not only did he hit it, and hit it well, he also placed it perfectly to thread the gap between mid-off and cover
another boundary, he angles down to third man and beats both the slip fielder and a diving fielder on the ropes
a much better ball, Mooney has been a touch short but he pitches up and the result is defence from the batsman
good ball to finish what hadn't been the greatest over, ten Doeschate defends to cover
good-looking drive to a half-volley, but he can't quite beat the field ... so just the one
a touch of seam movement in to the batsman, who defends with bat and pad right together. Half an appeal, but that was bat first
Ryan's on fire! Too full from Johnston and very wide too, the batsman leans into a cracking square drive, slicing it past a leaping point fielder. He hit that really hard
good batting, this wasn't there to be hit, nibbling away outside off and ten Doeschate leaves alone
another good ball, and patient stuff from ten Doeschate who leaves once again

well, he's tried to whip the bat inside the line so he can call this one a 'leave' but ten Doeschate was beaten by the away movement before he had moved his bat. This is an enthralling battle, ten Doeschate v Ireland

Kervezee gives it away! This really was such a soft dismissal, back-of-a-length on off stump and he just popped it straight into short extra cover's hands. He's better than that, Kervezee, and will be bitterly disappointed. Certainly not the greatest way to sign off at the World Cup, and Netherlands lose another
beaten outside off! Great ball, Mooney came much wider on the crease and then moved the ball sharply away from the bat. He had to play at it
beaten again, this time it's the bounce! Much shorter on off stump, Barresi cuts but is easily beaten on the top edge
fuller on off stump, defended into the covers
more defence from Barresi, he's easing his way back in
just short of a good length, he stands tall and chops down behind gully
tucked off the hip down and behind square on the leg side. Awkward bounce to deal with from Rankin, I'd certainly not enjoy facing him
speared down the leg side, Barresi sets himself for the glance but it's too far away and called wide
fuller, Barresi drives and the ball comes off a thick inside edge, rolling to mid-on
great length outside off, Barresi can't come forward to it and just taps to gully
the riposte! Was it the blow to the head or does he usually bat like this? A Happy Gilmour-style heave, and the ball rockets over square leg!
Rankin goes wider of off, Barresi steps across and leaves well alone
just a touch too straight, whipped firmly out through square leg but there's a fielder in the deep who charges round to cut it off
full on off stump, dug out towards mid-off. Mooney looks so much better when he pitches it up, too often he bowls way too short and simply doesn't have the pace for it
there we go, a touch short outside off and ten Doeschate launces into a cut ... fortunately for Ireland a fielder gets himself in the way
dropped down between midwicket and mid-on, there's time for a quick single
Mooney was very excited for a moment there, but cut his appeal for lbw short when he noticed the massive inside edge
a golf-swing from Barresi, but the ball goes in the opposite direction to that intended! He was aiming over wide long on, but a thick edge took the ball down to third man
full, driven out to the cover sweeper
good start, full and straight and defended
driven hard to mid-on, Barresi's looking to be positive
almost! Flighted up bravely by Dockrell, the ball drifted in through the air and took a thick inside edge into the pad ... hands on head for the bowler
up and over mid-off! He was always going to have a go with the field up. Strong shot
tossed up again, defence this time
again he gives the bowler the charge, but Dockrell spots him coming and drags the length down ... Barrsi doesn't get to the pitch but lays bat on ball to pick up one to cover
full on off stump, tapped back to the bowler who palms it away to leg
too short, Barresi is onto the pull in a flash. Played off the front foot, he had the look of AB de Villiers when he played the stroke
flashed square on the up, point dives across to cut it off
angled off the outer edge down to third man
full on off stump and angling in ... a hopeful appeal from Mooney as ball hits pad then bat, but he was outside the line
Mooney goes wide of the crease, sending the ball in towards middle and off on the angle ... but it's solidly defended
big appeal from Dockrell! That was hit on the pad but probably not straightening enough
the bowler gives it some air again, ten Doeschate defends down the track
tossed up on the toes, flicked to short fine leg
this is great stuff from Dockrell, real classical spin bowling with plenty of flight and guile. Barresi bends into a slog sweep, lays nothing on it
full, cracked very hard back at the bowler, along the ground
Barresi shuffles down and nudges the ball behind square on the leg side for another single
swept hard, but straight to short fine
tapped down to long-on off the back foot
tapped down to gully
nudged into the leg side
defended back to the bowler
dropped down behind square, very close in but the placement is there for a quick single
ooh, that could so easily have snuck through! Off the inside half of the bat and into the leg side
down the track, this time he beats the straight midwicket for one
punched hard down the ground, and straight too ... just the one though

swept with tremendous power out to deep midwicket! The ball was looped up again, and this time he middled the shot. There were men at long on and deep square ... and now they're plugging the gap at midwicket too
pitched up, in the slot outside off, fetched it and slog-swept it meatily over deep midwicket for a six, cleared the ropes comfortably
went straight on, short of a good length outside off, he played for the turn, inside the line, but it beat him
short outside off, makes room and cuts it through point into the deep for a single
good length outside off, drops it in front of cover, steals a quick single
closes the face on that and turns it into the leg side
tickled into the leg side for a single to raise the 50 stand
worked away behind square off the front foot
charged out of the crease, Dockrell saq him coming and held back his length, defended into the off side
pushed back towards the bowler, Dockrell dives to his right, he's in some pain now
short of a length outside off, tries to cut, gets some good bounce as it nips in, misses
short and wide, goes for the cut again, plenty of width but it's fielded brilliantly at point as the fielder hurls himself to his right and keeps them down to a single
back of a length on the off, gets on the back foot and drops it in front of the bowler
shortish outside off, gets back and knocks it down in front of point
bowled on a good length on the off, pushed back to the bowler
pitched up outside off, in the driving zone, drives at it hard, gets a thick outside edge to the boundary
good length on middle, pushed back firmly to the bowler
slightly short outside off, nips back in, gets behind it and drops it into the off side
they've ran well between the wickets, drops it in front of point, played gently and there is enough time to come back for the second
much closer to the off stump, guides it down towards short third man
gets on the back foot and works it down towards midwicket
whips it off the back foot to short fine leg

Review: Appeal for lbw, it's bowled on a good length, he walks across to turn it square, turns in, he misses, and is caught in front. Doctrove's the umpire, he raises his finger immediately. Barresi wants a review, but he's gonna have to go. That was out. Landed in line, struck him in line and was hitting middle and off.
fires it full outside off, tries to dig it out behind point, evades slip as it jumps off the pitch and they snatch a bye
short of a good length outside off, withdraws after initially thinking of playing at it
back of a length, guides it behind point for a single
nicely done, just closes his face there and plays it gently past the vacant square leg area, senses a chance to come back for the second and does so easily in the end
turned away behind square for a single
slightly short outside off, guided down towards third man for an easy single
angled in, worked away through the leg side for a single
lands on a good length, defended cautiously towards cover
gets forward, bends low and drops it into the leg side
stepped out of the crease, came down the track to turn it into the leg side, Stirling held back the length
shortish outside off, rocks back and punches it towards extra cover for a single
flighted on the off, rocks forward and drops it into the leg side
short and wide, cut away off the back foot to deep point for a single
poor line, Rankin fires that on leg stump and Borren has no trouble flicking it over square leg, there's a yawning gap there and he finds it
a touch fortunate this time, pitched up outside off and he pokes at it, gets a thick outside edge that evades first slip comfortably, streaky but it works
follows that up with a wide down the leg side, a bouncer but a misdirected one
Rankin's bleeding runs this over, short, an attempted bouncer, short and wide and Borren upper-cuts it over the slips to the third-man boundary
tries to be a little cheeky again, but it doesn't rise up as much as the earlier one, beats the outside edge
another edge, down to third man for a single, played away from his body there and it appeared to nip back in but it lands safely
slightly short, Borren's playing a good hand here, makes room and guides it behind point for a couple more
deliberately done, wider than the previous one, there';s no slip, waited for it to turn and late-cut it to the third-man boundary, a very innovative innings thus far
fullish, pushed into the leg side off the front foot
fullish on the off, meets it with a solid defence
turning in from a good length, steps forward and defends it back to the bowler
quicker through the air, slightly short outside off, tries to repeat what he tried earlier in the over, misses and the keeper fumbles
ten Doeschate shines again, short of a good length, runs it down to third man to raise another fifty, living up to his repuation yet again
back of a length outside off, surprises him with the bounce there, leaves it be
banged in short on middle, pulled away to deep midwicket for a single
slower one bowled on the off, cuts back in, defended back to the bowler
pitched up on middle, driven down towards long-on for a single
Borren's turn to rotate the strike, works it wide of mid-on to make it to the other end
slightly short on middle, gets on the back foot and tickles it through square for a single
flighted on the off, gets to the pitch and turns it to midwicket
turns it past short midwicket for a single
played back to the bowler
opens the face of the bat and runs it to short third man
hit thigh on the thigh pad and the ball rolls away harmlessly
poor fielding, that's straying on the pads and he's smacked it through midwicket for a boundary
tickled past midwicket for one more
played in the direction of short midwicket
cracked towards long-off for a single
well done, just ndged into the leg side, deep square leg is a little deep and they run back for the second
tapped towards point for a single
turned away towards square leg
crunched down towards long-off
worked away in the direction of square leg
dropped in front of square l,eg
struck hard towards cover but fails to beat the in-field
cuts back in from outside off, dropped towards point, no run there

, was a toughie, nipped back in, caught him on the glove as he was surprised by the bounce, landed just in front of the keeper or appeared to, Niall O'Brien ran forward to clasp it but couldnt get there
played away into the off side
waits for it to get to him and runs it down to third man for one more
in the driving zone and he goes at it hard but can't connect, it moved away off the pitch and beat the outside edge
brushes the pads and he squeezes a single towards square leg
drilled wide of long-off, was a full toss and he creamed it but there was  fielder in the deep, just the single
gets forward and dabs it into the leg side
comes down the track and drives it to long-on
pitched up on middle, he senses a chance, midwicket is up and he struck it hard and over that fielder to beat wide long-on to the ropes
flicked uppishly but wide of midwicket, on middle, lands on a length, nicely done in the end, well wide of the fielder
angling in towards middle, gets across and turns it square into the leg side
goodish length on the off, gets across and drops it with soft hands into the leg side for a quick single
fullish on the off, meets it solidly with a front-foot defence
angled in on middle, drove it past midwicket, thought about coming back for the second as there was a slight fumble in the deep but he recovered quickly to hurl it back in time
tight line on the off stump, defended solidly into the off side
slower one dropped short outside off, slapped towards deep cover for a single
bowled it short outside off, punched towards deep cover for one more, nicely timed
the slower legcutter from the back of the hand, fished for it but missed as it kept low and rolled away

quick single, knocked it down in front of midwicket into the leg side, rushed for a single and made it comfortably in the end, Porterfield flicked an underarm throw at the striker's end but he made it easily
again, drops it into the off side and steals a quick one
another legcutter from the back of the hand, full outside off, steered towards point
you know it's a new one if it moves that way, lovely deviation off the pitch away from the batsman, he leaves it alone
meaty delivery on middle and leg, clipped off the pads towards deep square leg for a single
short of a good length outside off, fishes for it, getting some good bounce is Johnston, beats the outside edge as he chases it
and again, Borren is tempted to poke at it, in the channel outside off, beaten once more
on middle and leg, struck on the thighs as he tries to work it away, lobs up in the direction of square leg, picks a single

sweeting timing by ten Doeschate, came off the meat, was pitched full outside off, he stretches forward and just caresses it through extra cover, Andrew White slides to his and hauls it back in with his legs, good stop in the end
slower one bowled short outside off, cracked straight to point
a pretty quick outfield this, angled it on middle flicked uppishly through square leg for a couple more
crunched into the off side towards deep cover for one more

slower one and he was not particularly in control of that one, landed on a length and Borren chased it, slicing it over point, Johnston at third man is a little fine and he has to run a fair distance to his right to drag it back in, dives and keeps them to two, good commitment in the deep
mid-off is up and that's a length ball that's begging to be dispatched, full and he smacks that over the in-field for a boundary
worked away into the leg side for one more to keep strike
gets it to come back in a bit, struck on the ribs as he tries to force it into the leg side, they steal a leg bye as it rolls in the direction of point
bowls a beauty to squeeze that through the batsman, but he's overstepped there and it's a freehit, nipped back in to square him up
banged in short and ten Doeschate miscues an attempted pull, gets a top edge and it lands safely but not much damage done, just the single
banged in short, a bouncer, seemed a touch too high on first sight but it was a good ball, Borren ducked in time to evade it
short outside off, shaped himself up to play the cut but it bounced more than he expected, missed the outside edge
getting some good bounce is Rankin, short of a good length and Borren tries to repeat the cut, can't connect once again
banged in short again, evades it well this time as it nips back in, not quite a bouncer but a good, testing delivery nevertheless
shortish outside off, pushed towards cover off the back foot
on middle and leg, turns it away through square leg for a single
four, fine leg is up, drifting on the pads, juicy delivery and ten Doeschate helps himself to some easy runs there, glances it elegantly wide of short fine for four more
finds the gap again, erred in length is O'Brien, it';s too short this time and he's given him some width as well, slashed hard and past point to the ropes once again
pushed gently past extra cover for a single
an expensive return for Mr O'Brien, short and wide, was the slower one this time, Borren waited for it and slapped it hard over extra  cover, brings his half-century in style does the captain
Rankin erris in length this time, short outside off and ten Doeschate finds the point boundary again, short and he chops it down past the square fielder to beat third man to the ropes
pushed away into the leg side for a single
full and wide this time, steered down towards third man for a single

ten Doeschate is in top form, Ireland aren't learning from their mistake here, we've seen three such shots to the fence now in less than two overs, short and wide again, he stands tall and cracks it through point for four more

A century for ten Doeschate, his second this tournament and he'll hope this proves a match-winning one, tried to close the face on that one, got a bit of a leading edge but safe and past point for a couple to bring up the landmark
a single down to long-off
gets forward and drops it into the leg side
reaches forward and closes the face on that one
after two dots he goes airborne, looping in towards middle, takes a couple of steps forward and lofts it clean and neat into the stands behind deep midwicket

Stirling bowled it flat this time, ten Doeschate had made his mind up, came down the track and tried to clear long-off but it was mistimed, the ball was quicker and he couldn't quite connect well, found a perfectly placed long-off, Mooney taking a simple catch
short of a good length, eased past extra cover for a single to keep strike
full outside off, tries to blaze it through the covers there but can't connect
short outside off, dabs it towards point, no single on offer
slower one bowled short on the off, knocked down wide of cover for a single
banged it short on the off, Buurman gets behind it nicely and plays it to cover
beaten, short of a good length and angles in, he plays inside the line to that one as he tries to open the face, misses
comes back in sharply, was the offcutter, gets on the back foot and jabs it past midwicket for a single
beaten, doesn;t turn in as much as he expects, tries to run it down, misses
bowled flat and quick outside off, cracked uppishly wide of the outstretched arms of extra cover for a single
shortish outside off, waits for it to turn in, guides it to short third man
finds the gap with ease, short, waited for it to turn in again and cut it hard through point, there's a massive gap between deep cover and deep point
gets front and across and pushes it to midwicket
slightly short outside off, cut down to short third man, no single this time
comes down the track and has a wild swing, short of a good length but he failed to connect, looked unlikely to connect, was more out of desperation than anything
edged and four, streaky, short of a good length, pushes at it off the back foot with a slightly open face, there's no slip and it flies off the edge to the third-man boundary

lands safely, short of a good length and he goes for a mighty pull, it ends up being a miscue, lands wide of Kevin O'Brien running to his left at deep square leg, covered good ground but not quickly enough, he's not the quickest runner out there
short on the off and he backs out of that one
shortish, coming back in, tries to open the face there but is beaten

he's been fortunate and continues to be, short and Buurman charges down the track to slash that over point, flies off the outside edge to the third-man boundary, Mooney's unlucky, maybe he'll bloig about it for us some day
a couple wide of long-on, fullish, gets forward and chips it betweeb long-on and deep midwicket

big appeal for lbw, but they belatedly refer it when the umpire turns it down, the offcutter and he swung at it across the line, struck on the pads but it seemed as if he was struck outside the line, the replays confirm that. It's an on-field call. Doctrove got it right
comes down the track and converts it into a low full toss, driven straight to extra cover
slower one and it's a safe shot in the end even though he didn't connect well, pitched up and he cleared the mid-off fielder, not the best of timing but had enough legs to take it to the ropes
comfortable single to the extra-cover fielder who's at the edge of the circle
slower one bowled full on the off, pushed towards extra cover
Mooney's bad luck continues and he can only smile, short, Borren tries to cream that through point, gets a thick outside edge to the third-man boundary
bowled from wide of the crease, attempts a similar shot does the Netherlands captain, misses
slower ball dropped short outside off, bunts it past extra cover for a single
slower one bowled short on the off, dragged uppishly over midwicket for a couple in the deep
full outside off, makes room and digs it out to extra cover
he knows the field well, took the risk, was short of a good length, moved away and chipped it over mid-off, didn't look very attractive but it's deliberate and highly effective
lovely flick, Johnston bowled it full on the off and hewalked across to whip it through square leg for four more
he's eyed that gap, slower one outside off, he moves across and sweeps it past square leg for a couple more in the deep
the offcutter bowled short outside off, chopped behind point for a single
no stopping that, pitched on a length, Buurman dances down the track and absolutely murders that between mid-off and extra cover
on the pads and he misses out, tries to flick it fine but doesn;t connect

slower one, didn't pick it, had a wild swing, missed, Nial O'Brien collected and took off the bails but Buurman was still in. The batsman appeared to slip and O'Brien took off the stumps but Buurman held his balance
excellent fielding by Gary Wilson at deep midwicket, Borren picked it up beautifully but Wilson dived to his right and returned an accurate throw, they'd taken a couple in the meantime
he picked the slower one there but didn't connect as he tried to dispatch it over mid-off
tries to clear mid-off and does so, just about, length ball, doesn't evade mid-off by much but it's still a couple more for the Dutch, raises the 50-stand
tried the scoop but it took the bottom of the end and went over midwicket, fetched it from outside off, two more
slower one and Borren has to go, just drove at it gently, was looking to clear extra cover but didn't have the power behind it, found Porterfield at the edge of the circle at extra cover
short of a good lengh on middle, played back to the bowler
pitched up on middle, swipes it wide of midwicket for a single
full toss on middle, swung away to deep square leg for a single
short on middle, Bukhari moved across to pull it square, was struck on the thighs
aiming at the blockhole outside off, dug out wide of extra cover for a single
slower ball dropped short on the off, mistimes the pull to long-on for a single
full toss on middle, comes down the track and smacks it back to the bowler, will feel he missed out there
landed full on middle, Bukhari was rooted to the crease there but all he needed to clear the ropes was a chip, timed it beautifully to clear deep midwicket
mistimes a pull this time, short on middle, went for it, aiming at deep square leg, got it high on the bat but was fortunate as it landed safely, just a single

misses a full toss, fired it on middle, made room to crack it through cover, missed a straight one and it crashed into middle and off. But wait.. The umpire wanted to double-check if that was a no-ball and replays confirmed it was. Rankin's overstepped. Buurman still survives, and what's more he has a freehit
another no-ball from Rankin, full outside leg stump and Buurman swings and misses. This was a close call as his foot was just on the line, 300 up
no damage done, swings and misses for the third consecutive time does Buurman, full on middle and middle stump is out of the ground, but it was a freehit
drilled off the front foot towards extra cover at the edge of the circle for just a single
short of a good length on middle, swivels and pulls it towards deep square leg for one more
almost gets it in the blockhole, digs it out into the off side for a single
a short one first up, sways away from it, a dot ball
another short one, Buurman gives himself some roon and tries to swing him over midwicket, misses
one for the over, a slower one banged in short and Buurban sways away from it again, three dots in a row and this is the last over of the innings
short of a good length outside off, called a wide, reaches for it but wisely withdraws at the end to get the extra ball

another wide, too wide, called one, Buuman wants to steal a bye, Niall O'Brien collects, and opts to run down towards the stumps and take them out instead of flicking a throw, the ploy works and Buurman, who was sent back by Bukhari, was caught short. He has to walk back
run-out, Netherlands slipping up in the final over, dropped into the leg side, Mooney runs in from midwicket, collects and throws down the stumps at the non-striker's end to find Seelaar short

three run-outs, a team-hatrick, short ball outside off, slapped to mid-off, Joyce fields and returns a throw to O'Brien who takes off the bails, Bukhari had called for a single but was sent back, another one goes
four in four, swung away towards deep midwicket, attempts an impossible second run, it's an accurate throw to the keeper who takes off the bails to beat Bukhari's dive

inn2.comm: sharp away movement from the batsman, it was full around middle, and then zipped away outside the off stump
tries to dismiss this shortish one through midwicket, but it is not short enough, and he mistimes the pull back to the bowler
another takes off and away from a length around off stump, he initially looked to cut but pulled out of the shot in the end
gets forward and tries to ease this one through covers but gets an inside edge on to pad
this time he gets it off the middle of the bat wide of mid off to get off the mark

Stirling begins with maximum, straight away, but nowhere close to where he intended to hit it, swivelled for the big pull over midwicket, got a steepling top edge that carried all the way over the slips, and over the ropes too, some mishit that, the ball was not short enough for the pull
bowls it short from round the stumps, he tries to bash it away off the back foot, right to extra cover on the edge of the circle
gets away with a short and wide one that Porterfield went back to and cut hard, but backward point got to his left and dived to save four runs
tossed this one up around off, that is the area to bowl, pushed away off the front foot
another short one, wide outside off, he cannot beat backward point with the cut
on the stumps this time, he goes deep to defend
and he gets away with a maiden finally, flighted a bit and it is eased away wide of the bowler
takes Bukhari on, that's the way Stirling knows, comes down the track, takes it as a high full toss, and lifts it over midwicket cleanly
sees this one pitching short and lines up for the pull, but it cuts back in sharply, and he steals a run as it rolls away on the leg side off the body
the captain is much more orthodox, gets forward nicely to a length ball to push it out to cover

dropped Raja at third man puts down a straightforward high chance, Porterfield went pulling a ball that was not short enough and outside off stump, got it off the toe end of the bat, the ball went steepling to Raja at third man, and right through his hands
another one down to third man, they are leaking runs in that region, Stirling gives it everything to one outside off stump, and the thick outside edge is too fast and fine for squarish third man

and another one, off the thigh pad apparently, Stirling went pulling one that was short and going down leg side, got enough on it to easily beat short fine leg, Netherlands are leaking runs all around
comes charging down the track, overbalances, almost falls over but manages to defend this one to short extra cover, and then gets back to safety

tossed up very full just outside off stump, he goes through with the forceful drive, gets it in the air, but short extra cover is too short to take those ones, and it flies past him and in to the gap past mid off
mistimes the cut in to the off side as this short one keeps low
played back to the bowler off the back foot
touch short, and wide again, he rocks back to cut it, but there is a man at sweeper cover now
turning in from outside off stump, he shuffles and plays it out in to the leg side
gets half forward and gets beside the line of this one outside off stump, and checks the drive to cover
again he stays beside the line, this one has some width and he cuts it ferociously, and gets it in the air, but in the gap past a desperately diving point
gets him to defend off the back foot with a back of a length ball
and again he offers some width outside off stump, this time he drives straight to cover
that is the way to dismiss the marginally short ones on a batting track, this one is on leg stump too, Porterfield is only too happy to rock back and pull it viciously in front of square leg
good reply from the bowler, draws Porterfield forward to one that is on a length, and bounces past his forward push outside off stump, didn't need to play at that really
waits for an instant, before deciding to pick this full delivery from outside off, with the turn, and wristily sends it high over midwicket
this one is even fuller, closer to off and slower too, got him to commit to that shot over midwicket again, bit of a slog sweep this time, he misses and the ball somehow misses off stump
lovely front foot drive, he invites him to drive outside off stump, and he does, getting to the pitch and easing it past cover
another boundary, same region, but this time off the back foot, just a bit short and he goes back and punches it pleasingly, not much power, outfield does the rest
works this full one with the turn wide of long on, Ireland are galloping
tossed up outside off stump, he gets forward and drives to extra cover
shuffles across and blocks this back of a length ball outside off stump
rush of blood, come charging down the track, and has a go at one that moves away from him outside off stump
going after everything, that's what he has been doing, slogs a fuller one away to deep midwicket
looks to force one from the crease and mistimes it on the leg side
pegs him on the back foot with a short of a good length ball, he pushes it back to the bowler
shot, gets to the pitch of a fuller one outside off and cracks it off the middle of the blade, but finds short extra cover in the way
stabs from the crease to one that cuts back in from an uncertain in-between length on off stump, gets a huge inside edge that cannons in to pad, Loots appeals frantically, wonder why
bashed, in the simplest of manner, front leg out of the way, stands in the crease and slogs a shortish one wide of midwicket, brutally effective at the moment
tries the same shot again, but this one is some way outside off stump, and he is beaten
and amid the violence, he now eases in to a glide to third man
cannot adjust to the left-hander on strike, bowls it on his pads, and Porterfield gleefully tickles it fine, just helps it on its way
gets the line right this time, around off stump, and he pushes it wide of extra cover
cramps him on the back foot with one angled close to off stump, and he pushes it away to point
turns it to midwicket and takes off for the single, but the man converges quickly to the ball, and Porterfield hurries back
smashes this one that gives him just a bit of width, but cover makes a diving stop to cut off the boundary
if you can't pierce the infield, then clear it with the lofted shot, that is what he does, gets a fuller one and lifts it over extra cover with a clean swing
pushed away in to the off side
Bukhari flicks the bails in his attempt to deliver from close to the crease, he tries to swing this full delivery through midwicket, mistimes it to mid on
no slip in place now, and Stirling collects four through that region, looks to have a crack over midoff but another thick edge flies fine on the off side

nothing edgy about this one, nothing streaky about this one, absolutely creamed, it was in his slot, full and on the stumps, and he swung it high in the air over deep midwicket, it took ages before it came down beyond the fence
and he splits the off side infield this time, no respite for the bowler, opens up a bit to get the placement right, and drives it wide of cover
almost got him there, length ball keeping low in the stumps, goner if he had missed, but he got some bat on it to pinch a single wide of backward point
Porterfield looks a paragon of non-violence in contrast to Stirling, eases into a silken push into covers
but even he can explode when he wants to, not quite brutal as Stirling but equally effective, drives a length ball outside off stump in to the gap past extra cover who gave up the chase pretty early
eases into the steer down to third man
goes up in appeal, but this one pitched clearly outside leg stump before striking him on the pads as he misses the waft across the line
pushed away in to the off side
goes for the dismissive pull again, and belts it off the middle of the bat too, but now there is a man in the deep in front of square leg
slows down the pace on this one, and he cannot work it in to the leg side
Stirling gets to his half-century now, striking 200 at the moment, plonks it in front of point for a single, second fastest one in the tournament, after Pollard
and he does so right away, tosses it up high outside off stump, it is squeezed down the track
pushes this one through quicker outside off, he gets in to a mess as he shuffles way outside off stump
gets a bit short, this one, and he slaps it away to sweeper cover
tosses this one up outside off stump, he comes forward to smother it
goes on the middle stump now, eased away with the turn towards midwicket
stays in the crease to a flighted one, could be dangerous, but gets down bat in time to steal a single in front of cover
looks to pull one angled across him that is not that short, off the bottom edge fine on the off side
cracks a confident drive this time, but it goes right to mid off
slapped away to covers, still cannot beat the packed off side in field
123.3 kph goes for the yorker, he digs it out towards extra cover
looks to force a fuller delivery through midwicket, gets too close to the ball, and hits it to mid on
can't get the high full toss away, pats it away to extra cover
picks a comfortable runs as he pushes a low full toss down to long on
lovely ball, goes straight on outside off stump, he was expecting the turn and was beaten as he had a waft, it kept low too
this time he turns it away to  deep midwicket
moves across a huge way outside off stump, and works this one backward of square
skips down the track, and is beaten in the flight, off the pads in to the off side
played out in to the off side
the one that cuts back in from short of a length has him in trouble, off the thigh pad in to the off side
whoa, he wanted to dispatch this one over midwicket, or did he, ended up playing a weak slog that rolled away to long on
cracked off the front foot, and they will collect a couple wide of sweeper cover
too full to ease in to the drive, which he tried to do, squeezed it away to extra cover in the end
they are doing as they please at the moment, this one is forced away to mid on from the crease
good delivery from Tendo, very full outside off, beats him as he tries to squeeze it away
can be risky but looks good when it comes off, he gets front leg way outside off stump, and sweeps a full delivery on the stumps to the deep square leg boundary
goes for the slog now, and gets it down to deep midwicket,
he skips down very gracefully and eases it away to long on
low full toss, initially surprised but recovers to hit it to long on
brings up the 100 with another comfortable run to long on
yet another single, Netherlands cannot plug the gaps at the moment, there are millions of them all around, he shuffles across outside off and works it through square leg
looks to lean in to the square drive, but it is too close to him, and he pushes it away on a bent knee
bosh! no niceties for this man, bends the knee and slams the full delivery, mid off is in the firing line
this one is in the air as he throws the bat at another wide one, but in the gap and away to sweeper cover
working nicely for Ireland this pair, Porterfield with his non-violent push towards extra cover, picks up the overthrow as the throw at the striker's in not taken cleanly
Stirling wants to scatter the off side infield with the inside out shot, but cannot get it past extra cover

now he does exactly that, stands in the crease, picks this one from a length, and plays the power forehand that gives extra cover and mid off no chance, who does the ritual of turning on his heels and attempting to give chase
drives a full delivery wide of a diving short extra cover
calmly done, shuffles across, plonks down the ball in front of midwicket and picks up an easy single
unfurls a smooth-looking front foot drive that goes wide of mid off
tries to flick this one on the pads, but gets it towards square leg, Ireland will take it
slashes hard on a bent knee, and spirits this one to third man
playing with a very open stance, adjusts to guide this one towards backward point
looks to launch in to the lofted shot over extra cover, but only the bat swung, the feet did not move, and he could not connect
gets to the other end this time with a single on the leg side
keeps a tad low around off stump, he pushes it away to the bowler
some width given outside off stump, and enough for him to drive to sweeper cover for the run
eep, don't see the need for that, but never know with Stirling, goes outside off stump, and tries to pick it cutely over fine leg, it goes down leg side

and no need to try being cute when he can hammer them like that, Tendo went for the yorker, he went deep in the crease and squeezed it forcefully in to the smallest of gaps between cover and point, super shot
he is getting repeated brain fades, blindly comes down the track, and tries to smash it down the ground, now only if he could connect that
and now they steal the single right in front of mid on, Borren cannot believe it
so much power in to that shot, stayed in the crease and hit a full delivery wide of deep midwicket who made good ground to his left
dropped Barresi lets one slip through his hands, Borren is looking distraught, Porterfield hammered the cut in the air, right at a catchable height to Barresi's left, and it burst through his hands
and then, it was that extra cover drive that was insult to injury, he got to the pitch of a length ball and sent it racing in to the gap past mid off, Ireland are on a huge surge
belted, if that word can be associated with William, too bad sweeper cover is in the way, and that will be his fifty
pinches the quick single in front of point, deft this time, and brutal mostly
goes for the big swing over midwicket, misses but still picks up the single
Porterfield has taken over from Stirling, has he, stays in the crease to a short delivery and flat bats it high over mid on, some bounces, and in to the boundary
driven stylishly off the front foot, but right to the bowler
ver low full toss, he adjusts, and pats it away on the leg side
another dropped chance, a tough one this time, Netherlands just cannot hold on, it was smashed over Tendo, he got both hands to it, but it few right through
skips down the track and  looks to have a huge swing over midwicket, but misses completely and takes it on the pads
eased off the front foot to the bowler
as if the dropped chances were not enough, now this one falls in between two men, extra cover and sweeper cover who charge in but his mistimed lofted shot drops short of both

goes for the leg before appeal, but it struck him way outside off stump, he was on the knee for that cute pick-up shot over fine leg, well a desperate Netherlands go for the review, it struck him a foot outside off stump, and would have hit the fifth stump, if there was one, what a wasted review
can Borren get in some tight overs, another straight one from round the stumps is pushed back to him
and he beats the bat this time, gets it to move away a tad from outside off stump, and Porterfield pushes inside the line
now he works a fuller one away through square leg with the angle
driven in the air from outside off stump down to long off
down the leg side, way down the leg side, and Stirling is in the mood, swivels and picks it wide of fine leg, almost went all the way
the 150 is up, what do Netherlands do, Stirling has another merry swing, and now he splits the gap between backward point and short third man
Tendo is not helping himself with this line, too much leg stump, too full, and Stirling picks it off the pads, short fine leg thought he had a chance, but it teased him all the way to the ropes
better from the bowler, length ball on middle, played away to midwicket
almost got another one, but this time short third man saved the boundary with a diving stop, it was guided and traveling fast
plays the Watson type chop-steer from close to the body, but it rolls away to point
a bit of width, and this time he steers it wide of third man
angled in on a length on off stump, meets the dead bat of the captain
turned away off the hip to fine leg
brave work on the sweeper cover boundary, parries away the ball just inches from the ropes with a big dive, it was smashed to his right with a big swing of the bat
all going Ireland's way, he gets a thick edge on the cut, and it flies very fine on the off side, four more
turned away from outside off to midwicket
this time he shuffles across and punches for a run to long on
tossed up wide outside off, turns away and beats him on the cut, bit of bounce too
hit back to the bowler off a fuller length
defended in to the off side
gives him the charge this time, but is beaten in flight and gets an inside edge to short fine leg as he looks to go over midwicket
hits this turning short delivery to long on off the back foot
fired in on middle stump, defended off the front foot
drags it short even as he charges down the pitch, and gets it down to long on with the momentum
tossed up generously high in the air, lovely revs on the ball, dips on the batsman who drives it down the ground
worked backward of square leg this time
waits in the crease to a tossed up ball, and punches it to sweeper cover in the end
pulled away backward of square leg from down the leg stump
silken drive along the ground to long off
caught in the crease, surprised by the turn and bounce, fends it on the leg side, Porterfield wills him in to the single
blocked off the front foot in to the off side
driven to extra cover off the front foot

finally Netherlands have a wicket, the extra bounce did him in, else a nothing delivery, short and miles outside off stump, he lined up for the cut, but the bounce meant he edged it in to the keeper's gloves, who is delighted, Cooper flashes a wide smile, Porterfield is furious
and that will be century for Stirling, shuffles across as has done so often, and picks a couple wide of deep midwicket, cheers all around
defended down the track off the front foot

Netherlands keep bowling long hops, and they keep  getting wickets, short, wide, sitting up, begging to be hit out of the ground, Stirling launched in to the pull, but picks out the man at deep midwicket, he is hugely disappointed as he walks back, hand on his head
flighted with confidence outside off, carefully patted away
Niall is away, another long hop, short and turning in, he rocks back, and cuts hard enough to beat cover
rolls away on to the leg side off the pads
carves this one away off the back foot and wide of sweeper cover
flighted very full, driven with the turn to sweeper cover again
runs this one with the turn wide of backward point, the non-striker isn't interested
defended off the front foot to the bowler
guides another one wide of backward point, cannot get the single
this time he will get runs, stretches forward and goes wide of sweeper cover
leans forward to smother the turn on this one
punched away off the back foot to extra cover
cannot get it past the off side infield, this time to mid off
tossed up outside off, he does not take the bait, blocked away, the difference a couple of wickets make
backs away to cut against the turn, pushed through quicker and could have been dangerous, goes to backward point
shuffles uncertainly to another flighted one, and in the end defends it off the front foot
turned off the pads straight to midwicket
tossed up very full, he pats it down the track
tries to break free with a forceful drive, but Netherlands have found new energy, extra cover dives to keep the strangle on
dug away down the track, still no single
he is getting impatient, skips down the track, and belts the drive, but cannot get it past mid off
finally he gets the single, down the ground to long on
down the track, but finds mid on with the drive, where have the runs gone? down the Hooghly?
and as soon as I say that. they re-emerge, lovely late dab from Joyce, gets it very fine, and that runs in to the boundary
backs away to cut away a flatter one to point
this is lovely touch work from Joyce, this one was a bit wider, so he went a bit squarer with the late steer, but had enough on it to beat the man at short third man
now he gets a comfortable single down to long on
gets away with a high full toss, he swings it away to long on
eased away past the infield to sweeper cover
and another one this time to Joyce, on the off side
almost beats him with flight and turn, he drives with a thick edge wide of short third man
driven away in to the covers off the front foot
goes on the back foot to a length ball, could have been tight, but he managed to cut it away towards point
this time he cracks a fuller one well wide of sweeper cover to collect two
comes lazily down the track and digs out a fuller one to mid on
flighted, driven with the turn down to long off
forces the tossed up ball wide of sweeper cover
tossed up high in the air, almost yorker length, dug out on the off side
pushed through flatter and fuller, he lunges out and drives it past cover
tries that delicate late dab again, but this time off the bottom edge in front of short third man, a single nevertheless
gets an inside edge on to pad as he comes forward to a length ball going across
not in a great position, falling away on the back foot, but still manages to pull the short one over midwicket, it is pulled back near the ropes
this time he will get it past the ropes, into  a good position, picks up one slightly short and sends it soaring over midwicket
goes fuller and he eases it away to extra cover

whipped away backward of square leg, they decide to take the second, clumsiness all around, Joyce's bat comes out of his hand, the keeper breaks the stumps, but fails to collect the ball cleanly, Joyce lives on
pushed away towards extra cover
cracked off the back foot, Borren with the diving stop at covers
pushed away to cover off the front foot
cannot get it away, rocks back on the back foot, and cuts it straight to cover
throws up the bait wide outside off stump, but he reels the bat in
breaks free with the slog sweep over midwicket, it was flat on the stumps, and he timed the forward movement and the swing perfectly
splits the off side field with the forceful cut but sweeper cover is on the boundary
crunching shot, Strauss-like cut, stands tall, eases away a bit and thumps it through point, good work by sweeper cover to pull it back
now he gets the single down to sweeper cover
driven off the front foot towards extra cover
after some millenia, a ball beats the outside edge, he looks to dab it away to third man outside off and misses
shot, marginally wide this one outside off and he spirits to the pitch and times it past a diving extra cover
shuffles across to a short one, takes it high on the thigh pad as he looks to work it away and it rolls away on the leg side
eased down the ground for a single to mid off, Ireland are chugging smoothly along
charges down the track and has a big heave at this fuller one, gets it off the inner half of the bat, and beats mid on who dives to his left but after the ball has passed him
goes on the pads with the angle, he clips it away through midwicket
very full around off stump, driven down to long off
some extra bounce on off stump, he comes out and defends off the high part of the bat
rolls away off the pads limply in to the leg side, this line is not helping Netherlands

Cooper gets another one, Joyce is walking, again that cut to a wide delivery, this one didn't bounce as much as the one that got Porterfield, but he had to reach out for the shot, and got the edge through to the keeper, neat take, Cooper cannot stop smiling
carefully patted away with the turn to midwicket
already he charges down the track for the big on, squeezes it out to the bowler
turned in to the leg side, still not single
and midwicket dives to his left to save what looked like a certain run, the crowd love it, this is a tight over
played out to midwicket for a wicket maiden, lovely stuff, Netherlands are hanging on by the tips of their fingers
goes straight on from round the wicket, strikes him on the pads, but going down leg
tossed up in the blockhole, he makes room outside leg and blocks it away
again he backs away, again he gets it in the blockhole, he tries to force it away on the off side, straight to extra cover
played out in the leg side this time
looks to break free with the reverse sweep, could have been close, he gets it off the glove and it rolls away fine on the off side
and now a leading edge makes an appearance, but falls well short of cover
shortish one, clattered off the back foot, but right to sweeper cover
phew, that just about missed off stump, he tried the reverse paddle from outside off, but it bobbed away close to the stumps
he is finally off the mark, and in some style, skips down the track, gets to the pitch and fetches maximum over the bowler's head
and again, gets to the flighted delivery, and sends it in to orbit straight down the ground, this will help the asking rate cool down
misfield at short third man, and by the time he recovers and gives chase, the ball trickles away in to the boundary, huge over for Ireland
turns in sharply from outside off stump, and he is hit high on the thigh pad even as he backs away
another short one turning away, and he cuts it wide of sweeper cover,
one more short and flat one, swatted away to long on, falling apart again for Netherlands
pushed through quicker, and blocked off the front foot
gets away with one outside leg stump with fine leg up in the circle, swept away to that man
luck continues to elude Netherlands, he got him to charge down the track and loft this one towards long on, but it fell just short
flicked away wide of the man at midwicket who dives but cannot prevent the single
starts off with a wide one outside off, guided neatly to third man
no luck for Borren, Niall backs away and has a huge swing at a fuller one, that edge is produced but finds no takers, scoots away fine to the third man boundary, no justice for the bowler
plonked down in front of the wicket on the off side
given width, will swing merrily, Niall does that, cuts hard and gets the ball past backward point, third man had no chance
doing it comfortably, another single down to third man
too much leg side, flicked wide of midwicket, inching closer all the time, can Netherlands find couple of wickets?
he will toss them up all day, slowly on off stump, patted away, dot ball, precious
sees him charge down, shortens it, he pats it back to the bowler, Seelaar rushes to field
skips down again, almost yorks him, ball dies in front of the crease, keeper rushed out, Wilson rushes back, pressure on
gets this one away finally backward of square
the match is rolling away from the Dutch, this time between Niall's legs, as he inside-edges a pull fine down the leg side
super over from Seelaar, cannot buy a wicket though, he tries the reverse dab, but straight to short third man, Wilson thinks the single will be too risky
got to feel for Netherlands, nothing has gone their way, he throws the bat at a full one outside off, and Buurman cannot get to the outside edge as the ball flies past him
couple more, slapped away wide of sweeper cover

Buurman holds on, stutters but holds on, went for the big pull, it hurried on to him, went steepling in to the Kolkata evening, when it came down Buurman was there, fell down but took it cleanly, it's that man Tendo who creates a crack of an opening, can Netherlands barge in?
but it is his brother on strike, keeps a cool head, lofts a fuller one over extra cover, sweeper cover manages to get there, does he touch the ropes, does he not?
squeezes this one wide of third man, another couple
blocked off the front foot, absolute coolness from Niall, Ireland need nothing else right now
full outside off, super delivery, patted away towards covers
another dot ball, cannot get it past mid on, full in length on the stumps
tossed up on the stumps, Kevin does not take him on, defends
goes for the big sweep, this is brilliant stuff from Seelaar, misses it completely
now he gets the single, through square leg, Niall comes on strike
gets forward on his knee, goes for the sweep, finds deep square leg, Seelaar all heart in the Powerplay, gets away with another tight over
goes charging down the track and across, the inside edge fetches him a single, how many of them have we seen, there is short fine leg, but Niall has his 50
gets a full one, flicks neatly, midwicket dives, but they have the single
makes room outside leg, Tendo follows him with a full one, driven in the air, point is in the way
the slower one, gets it right, he cannot beat point, Netherlands hanging in there
Niall skips down, another thick inside edge, flies to deep square leg, misfield, they run for it, precious runs
Niall does it this time, comes down the track, takes Tendo on, swings it over mid on, Ireland still look tense in the dressing room
Kevin tees off, Seelaar finally pays the price for consistently flighting it, the big man needs only two steps to get to the ball, it is picked up beyond the straight boundary
Seelaar continues to flight it, what heart, what guts, Kevin gets too much under the low full toss, gets a single to long off
Niall gets another single now, brings Kevin back on  strike

that will do for the Irish, Kevin gets down the track, reaches out to get to this flatter one, and lifts it over long off, that has disappeared, Kevin watches it go all the way, holds the pose like a golfer, Niall loves it, punches his bat, muted reaction from the big fella Kevin, just puts bat under his arm and walks back, Ireland have made a tall chase look mighty confortable, it's the O'Brien brothers to finish it off
